  "response": "On average, sumo wrestlers weigh between 250 to 450 pounds (113 to 204 kilograms), although some can weigh significantly more. The exact weight can vary widely depending on the wrestler and their division within the sport. Top-ranked wrestlers tend to be on the heavier side, often exceeding 400 pounds. It's not uncommon to find wrestlers who weigh over 500 pounds (227 kg) as well. The weight range is part of what makes sumo wrestling a unique and physically demanding sport.",
